Package com.google.android.agera

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ActivationHandler
    Receives events of the UpdateDispatcher created with Observables.updateDispatcher(ActivationHandler) when the first Updatable is added and the last Updatable is removed.
    Binder<TFirst,TSecond>
    A receiver of two input objects.
    Condition
    Determines whether a condition applies.
    Function<TFrom,TTo>
    Determines an output value based on an input value.
    FunctionCompilerStates
    Container of the compiler state interfaces supporting the declaration of Functions using the type-safe declarative language.
    FunctionCompilerStates.FBase<TPrev,TFrom>
    Methods allowed in both the FunctionCompilerStates.FItem and FunctionCompilerStates.FList compiler states.
    FunctionCompilerStates.FItem<TPrev,TFrom>
    Compiler state allowing to specify how the Function should modify single items.
    FunctionCompilerStates.FList<TPrev,TPrevList,TFrom>
    Compiler state allowing to specify how the Function should modify Lists.
    Merger<TFirst,TSecond,TTo>
    Takes two inputs and merges them into one output.
    MutableRepository<T>
    A Repository that can receive new data through Receiver.accept(Object).
    Observable
    Notifies added Updatables when something happens.
    Predicate<T>
    Determines a true or false value for a given input.
    Receiver<T>
    A receiver of objects.
    Repository<T>
    An Observable Supplier of data.
    RepositoryCompilerStates
    Container of the compiler state interfaces supporting the declaration of Repositorys using the type-safe declarative language.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.RConfig<TVal>
    Compiler state allowing to configure and end the declaration of the repository.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.REventSource<TVal,TStart>
    Compiler state allowing to specify the event source of the repository.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.RFlow<TVal,TPre,TSelf extends RepositoryCompilerStates.RFlow<TVal,TPre,TSelf>>
    Compiler state allowing to specify the next directive of the data processing flow.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.RFrequency<TVal,TStart>
    Compiler state allowing to specify the frequency of invoking the data processing flow.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.RSyncFlow<TVal,TPre,TSelf extends RepositoryCompilerStates.RSyncFlow<TVal,TPre,TSelf>>
    Compiler state allowing to specify the final synchronous steps of the data processing flow.
    RepositoryCompilerStates.RTermination<TVal,TTerm,TRet>
    Compiler state allowing to terminate the data processing flow following a failed check.
    Reservoir<T>
    A buffering mechanism that enqueues the values received via the Receiver interface and offers them back through the Repository interface.
    Supplier<T>
    A supplier of data.
    Updatable
    Called when when an event has occurred.
    UpdateDispatcher
    Passes on updates from an Updatable.update() call to any Updatable added using Observable.addUpdatable(com.google.android.agera.Updatable).
